**Environmental Monitor:**
The enviromental node collects data on local Temprature, Humidity and air pressure. These were as they are the primary data points used when monitoring micro climates in urban areas for urban development. The Environmental node collects data every 5 minute sending it directly to the data broker thingspeak and to the dash board whwere it can be analysed. The time and location of each reading is also recorded. Once on the dashboard the humity, temprature and pressure as all displayed. 5 minute intervals where choosen as the interval is not to long as to miss certain weather events such as cloud bursts.
The environemental node also saves each reading to a text file so that data is held locally incase an issue occurs with the data broker.
In order to send data to thingspeak it requires a client_id, username, password and channel_id. For this node these values are all encrypted using Fernet and saved within a txt file. THis has 2 primary advantages. It allows for the values to be changed without entering the code and when the program is run it prompts the user whther they would like to change these credentials. It also means that if a malicious actor ganes access to the device. No private information can be accessed.
In the dash board there as multiple threshholds set up that display warnings when suddon changes occurs in the environment around the sense node e.g. Rapidly rising temprature. All 3 fields also contain thresholds that when crossed display warnings that may represent errors in the system or exreme weather conitions/events.